It laughed "_Just give in and youll feel wonderful...._"

"_Nope~ We will just wait for your body to wake up or force it awake~_"
"Please don't force it awake, I haven't gotten enough sleep for a while." Shale points out.
"_Well you will not need to worry about that if you let us take over~_"
"...No, I really will." Shale struggles under the Goop's grasp. "I worry about a lot of things."
It tries to keep her pinned "_Well we will do the worrying for you...All you need to do is give in and you can relax~_"
"Relaxing... would be nice." Shale admits, and her struggles weaken a tiny amount. "But I got a revolution to run. You can't really do that... Wait. Wait wait wait. I have an idea."
"_What is it._" Its willing to hear her out

"You pilot my body long enough to possess the Plasma we are fighting against. Morise. They're incredibly powerful, and a shapeshifter. You'd like that body, wouldn't you?" Shale closes her eyes and prays this will work.

"Ah. Morise is easier to shape. They have thousands of possible forms. They can fly, melt into the shadows. Their body is like clay, yet powerful and strong."

It envelopes her and a sense of tiredness washes over her
Shale sighs and lets herself fall back. *At least I can kind of sleep now...*

"....We....are scared of him...We really dont want to harm anyone. But everyone kept attacking us when we hadn't attacked. We had....to defend ourselves...."
"I understand." Shale looks tired. Tired and sad.
"Please. Use my body as a host for. However long you need." She idly picks at the grass. *Autophobia*. "I don't mind."
"....I think your fiancees need you right now."
"I don't. I don't want to deal with things right now. I need a break."

It takes over, making sure shes comfortable in her mind. Its gonna help Shales fiancee's.
